President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of New York due to severe storms and flooding that occurred from August 13 to August 15, 2018. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement State, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The counties of Broome, Chemung, Chenango, Delaware, Schuyler, Seneca, and Tioga are eligible for federal funding for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures statewide are also eligible for federal funding. Seamus K. Leary has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made if requested by the State and further damage assessments warrant it. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.